WEBVTT

00:00:28.614 --> 00:00:30.696
Welcome to our library studio here as part

00:00:30.716 --> 00:00:32.176
of the Yahowah blog.

00:00:32.476 --> 00:00:37.439
I am here with our guest co-host, Wookie,

00:00:37.579 --> 00:00:40.262
and we are ready to dive back into

00:00:40.301 --> 00:00:42.021
the Eighty-Ninth Mizmowr.

00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:43.222
The Eighty-Ninth Mizmowr, of course,

00:00:43.662 --> 00:00:44.664
for those who have listened to this

00:00:44.704 --> 00:00:46.445
program over a period of time,

00:00:46.685 --> 00:00:48.206
you know that it is my favorite.

00:00:48.426 --> 00:00:52.787
There's no psalm, no proverb, no...

00:00:53.905 --> 00:00:54.786
prophecy,

00:00:54.865 --> 00:00:59.508
no Towrah chapter that I find is as

00:01:00.808 --> 00:01:05.111
inspiring, as enlightening, as affirming,

00:01:06.753 --> 00:01:09.233
as prophetically important, really,

00:01:09.474 --> 00:01:10.674
as the Eighty-Ninth.

00:01:11.995 --> 00:01:13.117
And one of the things we have learned

00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:16.197
quite recently is that the author of the

00:01:16.257 --> 00:01:20.141
Eighty-Ninth is not a relevant character.

00:01:20.721 --> 00:01:23.522
He is Ethan Ha Ezrachy.

00:01:24.709 --> 00:01:28.691
He was inserted into this position by Yahowah

00:01:28.751 --> 00:01:30.331
for this particular purpose.

00:01:31.173 --> 00:01:33.593
This Mizmowr was a collaborative effort.

00:01:34.733 --> 00:01:37.974
It's also true that Ethan plays a

00:01:38.055 --> 00:01:40.456
significant role in the introduction of

00:01:40.516 --> 00:01:44.358
the Mizmowr and says some things that are

00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:45.237
really interesting,

00:01:45.257 --> 00:01:47.078
and there's some things that he says about

00:01:47.278 --> 00:01:48.239
Dowd, about himself,

00:01:48.278 --> 00:01:49.359
and mostly about Yahowah.

00:01:50.439 --> 00:01:54.042
And then there is a two statement opening

00:01:54.462 --> 00:01:57.063
Salvo from Yahowah regarding his beloved

00:01:57.102 --> 00:01:57.322
son,

00:01:58.343 --> 00:02:03.025
followed by more insights from Ethan Ha

00:02:03.084 --> 00:02:03.486
Ezrachy

00:02:04.006 --> 00:02:06.066
And then we reach the point where it

00:02:06.307 --> 00:02:09.487
is really from the eighteenth and

00:02:09.508 --> 00:02:10.868
nineteenth statement.

00:02:12.824 --> 00:02:14.205
through very close to the end.

00:02:14.965 --> 00:02:16.665
It is all in Yahowah's voice and it

00:02:16.705 --> 00:02:17.887
is profoundly important,

00:02:17.907 --> 00:02:19.146
the things that he has to say.

00:02:19.948 --> 00:02:20.848
They're irrefutable,

00:02:20.867 --> 00:02:22.008
they're non-transferable,

00:02:22.748 --> 00:02:23.468
they're emphatic.

00:02:24.030 --> 00:02:26.670
And this Psalm,

00:02:27.912 --> 00:02:30.233
completely and without reservation

00:02:30.353 --> 00:02:32.913
obliterates the religions of Judaism and

00:02:32.932 --> 00:02:33.592
Christianity.

00:02:33.612 --> 00:02:36.753
There is literally no room whatsoever for

00:02:36.813 --> 00:02:39.055
either religion in light of what God says

00:02:39.194 --> 00:02:40.474
about David.

00:02:41.194 --> 00:02:42.715
And so we'll jump right back into it.

00:02:42.895 --> 00:02:45.415
I do want you to know that there

00:02:45.455 --> 00:02:48.296
is more to this than meets the eye

00:02:48.937 --> 00:02:49.217
and that

00:02:50.860 --> 00:02:53.361
Dowd is a very complex individual.

00:02:53.923 --> 00:02:56.125
He is exceptionally bright,

00:02:57.105 --> 00:03:00.688
quite articulate, definitely passionate,

00:03:02.409 --> 00:03:03.711
absolutely courageous,

00:03:04.472 --> 00:03:06.432
but he also has some rough edges,

00:03:06.674 --> 00:03:07.554
lots of them.

00:03:08.235 --> 00:03:11.258
And this was delivered during the roughest

00:03:11.298 --> 00:03:12.177
patch of his life.

00:03:12.639 --> 00:03:15.981
He was so far from what he

00:03:17.585 --> 00:03:18.185
could have been,

00:03:18.305 --> 00:03:20.165
should have been at this point,

00:03:20.746 --> 00:03:22.645
that he and Yahowah were not even talking.

00:03:23.486 --> 00:03:25.426
God's communications with him were all

00:03:26.388 --> 00:03:26.888
indirect.

00:03:26.987 --> 00:03:29.288
As for example, in this particular case,

00:03:29.688 --> 00:03:32.308
Yahowah revealed his sentiments toward

00:03:32.609 --> 00:03:32.968
Dowd,

00:03:33.830 --> 00:03:40.171
and the person named as Ethan ha 'Ezrachy

00:03:40.951 --> 00:03:41.451
delivered them.

00:03:42.594 --> 00:03:44.137
And I think that he was around for

00:03:44.176 --> 00:03:45.758
a good portion of Dowd's life.

00:03:45.818 --> 00:03:47.939
I think he appeared initially as Obed-Edom

00:03:48.621 --> 00:03:51.243
and that he had some role in his

00:03:51.283 --> 00:03:56.168
tutelage of Solomon before Solomon also

00:03:56.568 --> 00:03:58.730
went the way of his father and became

00:03:58.770 --> 00:04:01.312
way too interested in women,

00:04:01.554 --> 00:04:03.895
not for the right reasons,

00:04:03.955 --> 00:04:06.497
not for their brains or contribution or

00:04:06.538 --> 00:04:06.959
character.

00:04:07.676 --> 00:04:08.817
but for, well,

00:04:08.858 --> 00:04:10.377
you can imagine what else he might have

00:04:10.397 --> 00:04:11.138
been interested in.

00:04:12.158 --> 00:04:13.800
And this was the same problem with Dowd,

00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:15.120
particularly with Bathsheba.

00:04:15.180 --> 00:04:18.901
He did not choose wives or lovers well.

00:04:20.341 --> 00:04:21.882
It was not his strength.

00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:25.783
And he tripped badly over his choice for

00:04:27.105 --> 00:04:29.346
Bathsheba, who was not good for him,

00:04:29.406 --> 00:04:31.906
for Israel, for the covenant relationship,

00:04:32.026 --> 00:04:33.208
or for anything else.

00:04:34.028 --> 00:04:36.468
And this was a wake-up call for him.

00:04:38.370 --> 00:04:41.110
The good news is we prevailed.

00:04:41.911 --> 00:04:42.790
We got his attention.

00:04:43.651 --> 00:04:44.872
Dowd came back online.

00:04:45.091 --> 00:04:46.773
He accepted who he was.

00:04:46.872 --> 00:04:49.673
He realized what was laid before him,

00:04:49.812 --> 00:04:51.694
that he would be the Passover lamb,

00:04:51.713 --> 00:04:55.175
that he would fulfill Chag Matsah.

00:04:55.595 --> 00:04:57.295
He would take our guilt into shield on

00:04:57.336 --> 00:05:00.997
Matsah to make us and he not guilty.

00:05:02.014 --> 00:05:03.413
So it was a big responsibility that he

00:05:03.434 --> 00:05:05.935
was accepting and he would come back as

00:05:05.954 --> 00:05:07.975
a result of as king of the world.

00:05:08.536 --> 00:05:10.956
And what's remarkable is that Yahowah was

00:05:10.997 --> 00:05:15.298
so certain that we would prevail with this

00:05:15.358 --> 00:05:23.860
song that he actually goes right back to

00:05:23.940 --> 00:05:26.362
the firmness of his position with Dowd.

00:05:27.081 --> 00:05:28.682
That Dowd will be the one through whom

00:05:28.742 --> 00:05:29.083
he will

00:05:31.103 --> 00:05:31.543
create,

00:05:31.884 --> 00:05:34.365
literally cut the covenant relationship

00:05:34.406 --> 00:05:36.266
that Dowd will be his coworker going

00:05:36.307 --> 00:05:37.648
forward on all the things that need to

00:05:37.668 --> 00:05:39.288
be accomplished through the Mow'ed Miqra'ey and

00:05:39.329 --> 00:05:42.591
returning as king to govern the millennial

00:05:42.610 --> 00:05:43.031
Shabbat.

00:05:44.151 --> 00:05:48.413
He is a hundred percent back in with

00:05:48.473 --> 00:05:48.774
Dowd,

00:05:49.274 --> 00:05:51.235
which means that God would not have made

00:05:51.276 --> 00:05:52.016
these statements

00:05:52.954 --> 00:05:55.596
if he was not assured that this remedy

00:05:55.617 --> 00:05:56.036
would work.

00:05:56.476 --> 00:05:59.139
And so, you know,

00:05:59.158 --> 00:06:00.620
while it is tense and while I want

00:06:00.639 --> 00:06:01.720
to bring it to you in the full

00:06:01.740 --> 00:06:02.961
flavor of what God said,

00:06:03.680 --> 00:06:05.622
I also want you to know that we

00:06:05.682 --> 00:06:06.142
prevailed.

00:06:07.158 --> 00:06:10.259
The plan played out as it was articulated.

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:12.641
So in the third statement is the first

00:06:12.822 --> 00:06:14.903
time that God speaks directly to us.

00:06:15.723 --> 00:06:17.846
It's going to be the primary thrust of

00:06:17.906 --> 00:06:19.726
the Mizmowr before very long.

00:06:20.466 --> 00:06:22.309
But after a introduction by

00:06:23.745 --> 00:06:24.887
Ethan ha 'Ezrachy,

00:06:25.547 --> 00:06:27.728
which means that he is a perpetually

00:06:28.629 --> 00:06:29.728
deployed individual,

00:06:29.769 --> 00:06:32.190
that he is inserted in and out of

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:36.833
the timeline when needed to make certain

00:06:36.853 --> 00:06:37.374
that God's

00:06:39.197 --> 00:06:42.738
people and plan stay on pace.

00:06:43.218 --> 00:06:45.420
And that's precisely what his name means.

00:06:45.459 --> 00:06:47.500
That is what it conveys to us.

00:06:47.521 --> 00:06:49.382
That's what should be understood about

00:06:49.422 --> 00:06:49.581
him.

00:06:50.521 --> 00:06:52.382
He was the author of the thirty of

00:06:52.423 --> 00:06:56.543
the thirty-one Proverbs and five songs,

00:06:56.684 --> 00:06:59.704
this being the most dramatic,

00:06:59.745 --> 00:07:00.706
most important of them.

00:07:01.266 --> 00:07:03.507
So God speaks to us in first person

00:07:04.086 --> 00:07:05.127
in the third statement.

00:07:05.187 --> 00:07:07.148
It reads, I have established

00:07:08.103 --> 00:07:09.744
cutting through separation, karat.

00:07:09.803 --> 00:07:12.324
Karat's a very important verb in Hebrew.

00:07:13.305 --> 00:07:15.526
When God speaks of his covenant and the

00:07:15.565 --> 00:07:16.646
inception of his covenant,

00:07:17.226 --> 00:07:18.966
he always uses karat.

00:07:20.067 --> 00:07:22.649
And karat is not the same word as

00:07:22.728 --> 00:07:24.069
create, that would be bara.

00:07:24.728 --> 00:07:27.870
It is not the same word as made,

00:07:28.891 --> 00:07:29.290
asha,

00:07:29.310 --> 00:07:32.952
the word that would communicate that he

00:07:32.992 --> 00:07:34.673
has engaged in or acted upon.

00:07:35.333 --> 00:07:36.173
He used...

00:07:37.233 --> 00:07:40.836
Karat and karat literally means to cut.

00:07:41.538 --> 00:07:43.259
Now we would say in English,

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:44.581
we cut a deal, right?

00:07:45.702 --> 00:07:47.425
I'll cut you in on an agreement.

00:07:48.826 --> 00:07:50.908
So it's similar from that point of view.

00:07:51.769 --> 00:07:54.492
Karat is also used in connection with the

00:07:54.572 --> 00:07:55.293
circumcision.

00:07:56.353 --> 00:08:01.218
So it means to create by cutting off,

00:08:01.298 --> 00:08:04.081
by establishing through separation.

00:08:04.721 --> 00:08:06.124
So with karat,

00:08:06.144 --> 00:08:08.925
you know that this arrangement that is

00:08:08.985 --> 00:08:11.307
being established and cut,

00:08:12.593 --> 00:08:14.814
literally is a line in the sand,

00:08:14.975 --> 00:08:17.055
a chisel mark and stone.

00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:19.156
And you are one side or the other

00:08:19.237 --> 00:08:19.497
of it.

00:08:20.718 --> 00:08:23.019
You're either in or you're out.

00:08:23.319 --> 00:08:25.279
There is no straddling the line.

00:08:25.300 --> 00:08:27.821
There is no moving back and forth.

00:08:27.841 --> 00:08:28.122
You're in.

00:08:29.021 --> 00:08:29.822
or you're out.

00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:31.723
So I have established cutting through

00:08:31.783 --> 00:08:32.423
separation.

00:08:33.104 --> 00:08:35.306
I have created making a resolution by

00:08:35.365 --> 00:08:35.946
cutting off,

00:08:36.025 --> 00:08:37.986
as in the case of circumcision,

00:08:38.106 --> 00:08:40.128
a solemn agreement between the parties

00:08:40.148 --> 00:08:41.948
with stipulations, responsibilities,

00:08:42.089 --> 00:08:42.830
and benefits.

00:08:43.470 --> 00:08:43.830
And this,

00:08:43.889 --> 00:08:46.111
the thing that I have established cutting

00:08:46.131 --> 00:08:49.533
through separation is the Beryth covenant

00:08:50.014 --> 00:08:51.254
for the family.

00:08:52.914 --> 00:08:53.395
And he says,

00:08:53.535 --> 00:08:57.097
I have done so through my Bachyr,

00:08:58.320 --> 00:09:03.503
Ani, which would be through my chosen one.

00:09:03.582 --> 00:09:06.144
On behalf of the individual that I have

00:09:06.205 --> 00:09:07.426
personally decided upon,

00:09:07.466 --> 00:09:08.586
that I have preferred,

00:09:08.625 --> 00:09:10.707
that I have selected under the auspices of

00:09:10.748 --> 00:09:11.128
free will,

00:09:11.168 --> 00:09:13.589
the one I favor for a special relationship

00:09:13.708 --> 00:09:16.471
and affections from Bakar to choose to

00:09:16.510 --> 00:09:20.133
decide and from bachan to test,

00:09:20.754 --> 00:09:22.735
examine and scrutinize.

00:09:24.216 --> 00:09:26.096
Now that's a big statement.

00:09:27.619 --> 00:09:31.279
that the covenant has been established

00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:33.799
through someone,

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:37.360
one individual that God chose.

00:09:38.562 --> 00:09:39.701
Guess who God didn't choose?

00:09:40.761 --> 00:09:41.581
Jesus.

00:09:42.361 --> 00:09:43.822
Guess who God didn't choose?

00:09:44.842 --> 00:09:45.623
Bar Kokhba.

00:09:46.202 --> 00:09:47.364
Guess who God didn't choose?

00:09:48.043 --> 00:09:50.203
Mohammed.

00:09:50.224 --> 00:09:51.504
Guess who God did choose?

00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:55.245
Dowd.

00:09:55.264 --> 00:09:56.846
Should be all there wrote of,

00:09:57.727 --> 00:09:58.668
Those three religions,

00:09:58.688 --> 00:10:02.113
they're all gone with that one statement.

00:10:02.133 --> 00:10:04.195
Because God's going to name the person

00:10:04.215 --> 00:10:06.356
that he chose as Dowd.

00:10:07.177 --> 00:10:10.041
And the covenant is the essence of the

00:10:10.120 --> 00:10:10.461
Towrah.

00:10:12.958 --> 00:10:14.639
Look at the book, Bare’syth,

00:10:14.759 --> 00:10:17.159
after he gets through creation and the

00:10:17.220 --> 00:10:20.321
flood, it goes directly to the formation,

00:10:20.341 --> 00:10:22.480
that whole narrative with Abraham and

00:10:22.561 --> 00:10:25.162
Sarah to conceive the covenant

00:10:25.221 --> 00:10:25.961
relationship.

00:10:26.081 --> 00:10:28.282
And it goes some twelve,

00:10:28.322 --> 00:10:30.842
fourteen chapters through the initial

00:10:30.883 --> 00:10:31.102
book.

00:10:31.123 --> 00:10:32.062
So you have creation,

00:10:32.082 --> 00:10:34.102
you have the experience in Eden,

00:10:34.224 --> 00:10:36.063
you have the flood.

00:10:37.210 --> 00:10:38.351
Each of those, by the way,

00:10:38.532 --> 00:10:40.173
mirror the covenant itself.

00:10:40.735 --> 00:10:42.998
Then you have the covenant and then you

00:10:43.018 --> 00:10:46.302
have how the covenant plays out through

00:10:46.682 --> 00:10:51.450
Yitschaq and through Jacob and the sons of

00:10:51.629 --> 00:10:52.130
Yisrael.

00:10:53.453 --> 00:10:56.456
So that is the entire story of Bare'Syth

00:10:56.517 --> 00:10:57.076


00:10:57.158 --> 00:10:58.899
It's Genesis.

00:10:58.979 --> 00:11:00.340
It's all about the covenant.

00:11:01.020 --> 00:11:03.403
It's the heart and soul of the Towrah.

00:11:03.423 --> 00:11:05.424
It's the cornerstone of the Towrah.

00:11:06.145 --> 00:11:06.245
Now,

00:11:06.285 --> 00:11:09.508
the covenant is more than just the central

00:11:09.629 --> 00:11:12.591
piece of the Towrah.

00:11:12.730 --> 00:11:14.273
It is the only way to God.

00:11:15.677 --> 00:11:17.197
Now, God has a specific path.

00:11:18.139 --> 00:11:22.221
It's Pesach Matsah Bikuwrym, Shabuwah,

00:11:22.261 --> 00:11:24.384
Taruwah, Kipurym, and Sukah,

00:11:24.884 --> 00:11:26.546
with the first three providing the

00:11:26.586 --> 00:11:27.626
benefits of the covenant.

00:11:28.287 --> 00:11:32.029
So the only way that you can participate

00:11:32.730 --> 00:11:35.393
in Pesach and have it be beneficial to

00:11:35.432 --> 00:11:37.575
you is to be in the covenant.

00:11:37.615 --> 00:11:38.174
And if you're a man,

00:11:38.195 --> 00:11:39.735
you have to be circumcised just to

00:11:39.937 --> 00:11:41.037
emphasize this point.

00:11:42.239 --> 00:11:44.660
And the guilt that's carried away on

00:11:44.721 --> 00:11:46.962
Matsah is that of the covenant's children.

00:11:47.143 --> 00:11:50.105
And firstborn children means that we

00:11:50.186 --> 00:11:52.268
become part of the covenant family on

00:11:52.288 --> 00:11:52.768
Bikuwrym.

00:11:53.509 --> 00:11:55.029
So literally,

00:11:56.211 --> 00:11:58.333
it is the covenant's benefits that are

00:11:58.354 --> 00:11:59.313
being delivered there.

00:11:59.994 --> 00:12:01.936
through the first three, Mow'ed, Miqra'ey,

00:12:02.395 --> 00:12:03.736
Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym.

00:12:04.697 --> 00:12:07.341
This means that Dowd fulfilled them when

00:12:07.421 --> 00:12:09.942
God says, I have cut through separation,

00:12:09.962 --> 00:12:12.845
having established the Beryth covenant for

00:12:12.884 --> 00:12:16.769
the family through my Bachyr, chosen one,

00:12:17.149 --> 00:12:18.389
and I have sworn an oath,

00:12:18.429 --> 00:12:20.412
which I will affirm this promise seven

00:12:20.471 --> 00:12:22.214
times over, because there are seven Mow'ed,

00:12:22.254 --> 00:12:23.434
Miqra'ey, to Dowd.

00:12:25.618 --> 00:12:26.258
Ebed Any,

00:12:26.498 --> 00:12:29.620
my authorized agent and coworker who

00:12:29.759 --> 00:12:32.902
serves with me.

00:12:32.942 --> 00:12:36.562
That is, again, that's all she wrote.

00:12:36.582 --> 00:12:40.965
There's no other option.

00:12:41.245 --> 00:12:46.128
It's the complete obliteration of

00:12:46.168 --> 00:12:47.408
Christianity, Judaism,

00:12:47.528 --> 00:12:51.210
and Islam with that statement.

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:51.870
There can be no...

00:12:52.759 --> 00:12:54.279
co-working Jesus.

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:56.759
There can be no savior Jesus.

00:12:57.640 --> 00:13:02.503
There can be no new covenant and there

00:13:02.523 --> 00:13:04.263
can be no covenant that is established

00:13:04.302 --> 00:13:05.884
with anyone other than with Dowd.

00:13:08.924 --> 00:13:10.826
And you can't transfer this because God

00:13:10.865 --> 00:13:11.725
said it's to Dowd.

00:13:14.793 --> 00:13:16.196
He didn't say it was to whomever you

00:13:16.216 --> 00:13:16.756
want it to be.

00:13:17.457 --> 00:13:19.041
He didn't say it's to Jesus.

00:13:19.140 --> 00:13:20.602
